People can say the meanest words. Others do things that hurt us and the people we love. I guess the worst thing that someone can do is betray us and our trust in them. This can hit you and me the hardest.

There are ways that can help us get through this difficult time . One important way is to TALK IT OUT  with people who support you, who listen, who see and feel your heart, who cry and laugh with you, who go with you to the feet of our Almighty Father. 
Going to church helps. Join a  small 'life' GROUP - this is  your support group where you can feel safe and accepted for being you. 
Attend THERAPY  counselling sessions if and when you can. 

FORGIVING  others and ourselves is hard work but it sets us FREE.

GOD is available for  you. You can be OPEN to Him, express anything to Him without fear of being judged. You can draw strength from Him. 
You  can cry out to Him anytime, 24/7. 

